answer:
In javascript we can access with:

* dot notation - `foo.bar`
* square brackets - `foo[someVar]` or `foo["string"]`

But only second case allows to access properties dynamically:

```
var foo = { pName1 : 1, pName2 : [1, {foo : bar }, 3] , ...}

var name = "pName"
var num  = 1;

foo[name + num]; // 1

// -- 

var a = 2;
var b = 1;
var c = "foo";

foo[name + a][b][c]; // bar

```

